sec.p:
As shown in Fig. 1, the sample S1 is the pure anatase TiO2 (JCPDS file no. 21–1272) when the calcination temperature is 350 °C but the phase purity of anatase TiO2 apparently decreases with the increasing calcination temperature. Structural transformation from anatase to rutile is detected in sample S1 after calciantion at 400 °C (JCPDS file no. 21–1276). However, there is no phase transformation occurred until 700 °C for Sample S2, S3 and S4. The phase content in samples can be calculated by the following equation48:2Rutilephase%=1001+0.8(IAIR)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
